cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with optical flow estimation, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The use of a fully convolutional network also suggests that it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) category. The paper also introduces lateral dependencies between neurons, which is a common technique in deep learning, further supporting the likelihood of it belonging to the cs.NE category. The use of multi-layer supervision and the importance of image contours suggest that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the fact that the proposed method is designed for use in robotics applications, as well as its performance on competitive benchmarks, suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) category.
